President Cyril Ramaphosa will update the nation tonight about efforts to curb the spread of COVID-19. His address follows a meeting of the National Coronavirus Command Council. PRETORIA - President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation on Thursday night on the efforts to contain the spread of the coronavirus The president is expected to speak at 8pm. The Presidency said Ramaphosa's address follows a meeting of the COVID-19 National Command Council held on Wednesday. READ: Ramaphosa defends WHO after Trump virus lashing Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.